data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Specify the AAD authority to be used for authentication (e.g. contoso.com). Depending on your tenant configuration, this may be optional, unless you're connecting with an application id in which case it is required:

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: When the local file system is selected as the source or the target, SyncKusto loads all of the files into a temporary database and then asks Kusto for the database schema. Specify a Kusto cluster and database to use for the comparison. You must be a database admin.

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: These settings are only applied when a file is written. They do not affect the comparison operation. To apply this to all existing files, delete all the files locally, execute the comparison again and then update the local files.
